questions.text: Fouchette is formed by the fusion of

questions.text: Uterine pain during labour is carried by
questions.solution:
Innervation of uterus

Sympathetic - T10 to L2

Superior hypogastric plexus (a) Presacral N

Parasympathetic - S2, 3, 4

Sympathetic + Parasympathetic forms -> Inferior hypogastric/Pelvic plexus which further divides into three plexus as follows.

  • Vesical plexus
  • Middle rectal plexus
  • Uterovaginal plexus also called frankenhauser plexus
  • Uterine Pain - carried by T10, 11, 12, L1
  • Cervix & Upper vaginal pain - S2, 3, 4 (Pelvic splanchnic N)
  • Lower Vagina - Pudendal N

questions.text: Eversion is
questions.solution:
Cervix:

  • Divided into Supra vaginal and Infra vaginal parts
  • Internal OS – corresponds to UV fold of peritoneum
  • External OS – Before child birth – Oval opening
  • After child birth – Transverse slit
  • Ecto Cx – Non keratinized stratified squamous epithelium
  • Endo Cx – Columnar epithelium (Single layer / mucin secreting)
  • Eversion – Columnar epithelium moving out & onto the ecto Cx
  • Cx has very little smooth muscle & mainly has collagen, elastin & proteoglycan

questions.text: Identify the false statement about fetal hematopoeisis
questions.solution:
Fetal Blood:

  • Early pregnancy – Megaloblastic & nucleated
  • Near term –Normoblastic
  • Up to 24 weeks – only HbF (α2γ2)
  • From 24 weeks onwards – Adult Hb (α2β2) + Fetal Hb
  • At term – 75 to 80% is HbF type
  • Other types of Hb found are grower 1, 2, Portland
  • Fetal Hb is completely replaced by adult Hb between 6-12 months after birth
  • Fetal Hb has low affinity for 2, 3 DPG & increased affinity for O2

questions.text: Which of the following is the most common type of Hb in fetal circulation

  • Bone Marrow – HbA from 24 weeks

questions.text: Myrtiform caruncle is a remnant of
questions.solution:
Vagina:

  • Non keratinized stratified squamous epithelium
  • Starts with hymen (membrane of varying thickness)
  • Hymen Transforms into myrtiform caruncles after child birth
  • Anteriorly separated from bladder & urethra by vesicovaginal septum

  • Anterior wall 6-8cm
  • Posterior wall 7-10cm
  • No glands
  • Has mucosa with rugae, smooth muscle, collagen & elastin

questions.text: Polyhydramnios is associated with all except
questions.solution:
Causes for polyhydramnios

  • Anencephaly
  • Hydranencephaly
  • Holoprosencephaly
  • Cleft lip/palate
  • Micrognathia
  • Barter syndrome
  • Neurological or Muscular etiology
  • Arthrogryposis, akinesia sequence
  • Myotonic dystrophy
  • Tracheal compression or obstruction
  • Neck veno lympathic abnormality
  • CHAOS
  • Thoracic etiology (Mediastinal shift)
  • Diaphragmatic hernia
  • Cystic adenomatoid malfunction
  • High output cardiac state
  • Ebstein anomaly
  • Tetralogy of fallot with absent pulmonary valve
  • Thyrotoxicosis
  • Cardiomyopathy, myocarditis
  • Cardiac Arrhythmi
  • Tachyarrhythmia: Atrial flutter, atrial fibrillation, Supraventricular tachycardia
  • Bradyarrhythmia: Heart block
  • GI obstruction
  • Esophageal atresia
  • Duodenal atresia
  • Renal Urinary
  • Ureteropelvic junction obstruction
